{# Simple, clean report template - WeasyPrint compatible #}
{% extends "base/simple_layout.j2" %}

{% block title %}Comprehensive Fecal Examination - {{ patient.name }}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{# Page 1: Title Page #}
<div class="page">
    <div class="diagonal-stripes"></div>
    
    <div class="title-page-content">
        <h1 class="main-title">COMPREHENSIVE<br>FECAL<br>EXAMINATION</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">DNA sequencing</p>
        
        <div class="pill-row">
            <span class="pill-box">{{ patient.name }}</span>
            <span class="pill-box">{{ patient.species }}, {{ patient.age }}</span>
            <span class="pill-box">Sample: {{ patient.sample_number }}</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="pill-row">
            <span class="pill-box">Received: {{ patient.date_received }}</span>
            <span class="pill-box">Analyzed: {{ patient.date_analyzed }}</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="pill-row">
            <span class="pill-box">Performed by: {{ patient.performed_by }}</span>
            <span class="pill-box">Requested by: {{ patient.requested_by }}</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <div class="footer-section">
            <img src="{{ config.assets_path }}/hippovet_logo.png" alt="HippoVet" class="logo">
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: center;">
            <!-- No page numbers for clean professional look -->
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: right;">
            <strong style="font-size: 12pt; color: var(--dark-blue);">MEMT LABORATORY</strong>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

{# Page 2: Charts and Results #}
<div class="page">
    <div class="content">
        
        <div class="section-header">SEQUENCING RESULTS</div>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--primary-blue); margin-bottom: 10mm; font-size: 16pt; text-align: center;">MICROBIOTIC PROFILE</h3>
        
        <div class="dysbiosis-index">
            <div style="font-size: 20pt; margin-bottom: 5mm;">
                Dysbiosis Index (DI): {{ "%.1f"|format(data.dysbiosis_index) }}
            </div>
            <div style="font-size: 14pt;">
                {{ data.dysbiosis_category|title }} microbiota
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="clinical-text">
            <p><strong>Interpretation:</strong> {{ data.clinical_interpretation }}</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">SPECIES DISTRIBUTION</div>
        {% if charts.species_distribution %}
        <img src="{{ charts.species_distribution }}" alt="Species Distribution" class="chart-img">
        {% else %}
        <p style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-light);">Chart not available</p>
        {% endif %}
        
        <div class="section-header">PHYLUM DISTRIBUTION IN GUT MICROFLORA</div>
        {% if charts.phylum_distribution %}
        <img src="{{ charts.phylum_distribution }}" alt="Phylum Distribution" class="chart-img">
        {% else %}
        <p style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-light);">Chart not available</p>
        {% endif %}
        
        <div class="section-header">PHYLUM COMPARISON WITH REFERENCE RANGES</div>
        {% if charts.phylum_comparison %}
        <img src="{{ charts.phylum_comparison }}" alt="Phylum Comparison" class="chart-img">
        {% else %}
        <p style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-light);">Chart not available</p>
        {% endif %}
        
        <p style="font-size: 9pt; color: var(--text-light); text-align: center; margin-top: 8mm;">
            Scale: 0-20 normobiotic; 21-50 moderate dysbiosis; >50 severe dysbiosis microbiota
        </p>
        
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <div class="footer-section">
            <strong>HippoVet Laboratory</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">Veterinary Microbiome Analysis Center</span>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: center;">
            <!-- No page numbers -->
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: right;">
            <strong>MEMT LABORATORY</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">www.hippovet.com</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

{# Page 3: Clinical Analysis #}
<div class="page">
    <div class="content">
        
        <div class="section-header">CLINICAL ANALYSIS</div>
        
        <div class="clinical-text">
            {% if data.dysbiosis_category == "normal" %}
            <p>Molecular examination revealed gut microflora properly balanced with minor deviations. The bacterial diversity and phylum distribution are within expected ranges for healthy equine gut microbiome.</p>
            
            <p>The predominant bacterial phyla detected show appropriate proportions:
            {% set sorted_phyla = data.phylum_distribution.items() | list | sort(attribute='1', reverse=true) %}
            {% for phylum, percentage in sorted_phyla[:3] %}
            {{ phylum }} ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}
            {% endfor %}. This distribution supports proper digestive function and immune system balance.</p>
            
            <p>The low dysbiosis index indicates a stable microbial ecosystem with minimal disruption to the normal flora composition.</p>
            {% elif data.dysbiosis_category == "mild" %}
            <p>Molecular examination revealed moderate imbalance in gut microflora composition. While not critical, this dysbiosis may impact digestive efficiency and requires monitoring.</p>
            {% else %}
            <p>Molecular examination revealed significant dysbiosis requiring immediate intervention. The severe imbalance in microbial populations indicates compromised gut health.</p>
            {% endif %}
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">RECOMMENDATIONS</div>
        <div class="clinical-text">
            {% for recommendation in data.recommendations %}
            <p>• {{ recommendation }}</p>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">LABORATORY EXAMINATIONS</div>
        <table>
            <tr><th>Test</th><th>Result</th><th>Reference</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Flotation method</td><td>No protozoan cysts detected</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Sedimentation method</td><td>No larval forms observed</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
            <tr><td>McMaster method</td><td>No parasitic eggs observed</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Occult blood</td><td>Negative</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
            <tr><td>pH</td><td>6.8</td><td>6.5-7.0</td></tr>
        </table>
        
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <div class="footer-section">
            <strong>HippoVet Laboratory</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">Accredited Laboratory - ISO 15189</span>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: center;">
            <!-- No page numbers -->
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: right;">
            <strong>MEMT LABORATORY</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">Tel: +48 123 456 789</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

{# Page 4: Additional Analysis and Educational Content #}
<div class="page">
    <div class="content">
        
        <div class="section-header">UNDERSTANDING THE EQUINE MICROBIOME</div>
        
        <div class="clinical-text">
            <p>The equine gut microbiome consists of trillions of microorganisms that play crucial roles in:</p>
            <p><strong>• Digestion:</strong> Breaking down fiber and complex carbohydrates</p>
            <p><strong>• Immunity:</strong> Supporting immune system and pathogen resistance</p>
            <p><strong>• Health:</strong> Producing vitamins and maintaining intestinal barrier</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">WHAT IS DYSBIOSIS?</div>
        
        <div class="clinical-text">
            <p>Dysbiosis refers to an imbalance in the gut microbiome composition that can lead to:</p>
            <p>• Digestive disorders (colic, diarrhea, poor feed conversion)</p>
            <p>• Increased infection susceptibility and reduced nutrient absorption</p>
            <p>• Inflammatory conditions and metabolic dysfunction</p>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin: 8mm 0; padding: 8mm; background-color: var(--gray-bg); border-radius: 5mm;">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom: 5mm; color: var(--primary-blue); text-align: center;">Dysbiosis Index Interpretation:</h4>
            <div style="margin: 3mm 0;"><span style="color: var(--green); font-weight: bold;">0-20:</span> Normal microbiome balance</div>
            <div style="margin: 3mm 0;"><span style="color: orange; font-weight: bold;">21-50:</span> Mild dysbiosis - monitoring recommended</div>
            <div style="margin: 3mm 0;"><span style="color: red; font-weight: bold;">51+:</span> Severe dysbiosis - intervention needed</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">MAINTAINING MICROBIOME HEALTH</div>
        
        <div class="clinical-text">
            <p><strong>Dietary Considerations:</strong></p>
            <p>• Provide consistent, high-quality forage</p>
            <p>• Minimize sudden dietary changes</p>
            <p>• Avoid excessive grain and high-starch diets</p>
            
            <p><strong>Management Practices:</strong></p>
            <p>• Reduce stress through consistent routines</p>
            <p>• Limit unnecessary antibiotic use</p>
            <p>• Provide adequate exercise and monitor digestive health</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section-header">IMPORTANT</div>
        
        <div style="margin: 8mm 0; font-size: 10pt; border: 1px solid var(--border-gray); padding: 8mm; background-color: var(--gray-bg);">
            <p style="margin: 0;">The presented result is a microbiotic profile of the tested sample. Microbiotic results should be interpreted in conjunction with clinical signs and other diagnostic findings. For optimal results, samples should be collected before antibiotic therapy.</p>
        </div>
        
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <div class="footer-section">
            <strong>HippoVet Laboratory</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">Veterinary Microbiome Analysis Center<br>Accredited Laboratory - ISO 15189</span>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: center;">
            <!-- Clean professional layout without page numbers -->
        </div>
        <div class="footer-section" style="text-align: right;">
            <strong>MEMT LABORATORY</strong><br>
            <span style="font-size: 8pt;">Tel: +48 123 456 789<br>Email: lab@hippovet.com</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}